ristianity, but a bit from [some other religion]&quot;, then you believe in a religion of your own, and you are blessed. For you have found your way of live, amongst a thousand fires willing to consume your mind with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    their</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> beliefs, and quench <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    your own</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> beliefs.<br><br>As for life's purpose, I think my brother came up with the best statement: &quot;There is no reason to live, but we like it that way!&quot; Which is true, in my opinion. We all try to find purpose to our lives, that we spend our entire lives <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    searching</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. We should concentrate on living as we please (within reason, or course), trying to enjoy life, but still make it enjoyable for our loved ones too. The origins of life will probably never be known to 100%. In the distant future, people will probably laugh at the foolish beliefs of &quot;science&quot; we have got now. Man will always make mistakes, be wrong, have the wrong theories and assumptions, and so Man will continue to do, into eternity...<br><br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    &quot;Live your life they way <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    you</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> want it, there is more than one dream.<br>Live your life they way <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    you</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> want it, there is more than one truth!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>--Henrik &quot;Aacheron&quot; Hansson, aka. 'Something Wicked'<br> <p><center><table><tr><td style=filter:glow(color="green",strenght="5")><font color="white"><center>Med skrik och skrän som tusen korpars rop</center><BR><center>Vi sliter oss fram ut ur berg och grop</center><BR><center>Klor vassa som svärd, käftar lik ulvens</center><BR><center>Fram kommer vättar, smaka vår eld</center><BR><BR><center>Vi dricka ert blod, vår livets saft</center><BR><center>Så mycket av det, v